{
  "comment": "Seccomp profile for watertwin-ingest. Default action is to deny (errno) any syscall not explicitly allowed, which shrinks the kernel attack surface exposed to untrusted-file parsers. The allowlist covers the syscalls needed by CPython, uvicorn, and the resource-capped parse sandbox (fork/exec of a child interpreter, setrlimit, setsid, kill for timeout enforcement). No syscalls that would be needed to reach a raw OT/control network are added beyond ordinary TCP client sockets, which are further constrained by the deny-all egress NetworkPolicy.",
  "defaultAction": "SCMP_ACT_ERRNO",
  "defaultErrnoRet": 1,
  "architectures": [
    "SCMP_ARCH_X86_64",
    "SCMP_ARCH_X86",
    "SCMP_ARCH_X32",
    "SCMP_ARCH_AARCH64"
  ],
  "syscalls": [
